   The Usual Desire to Kill: A Novel
   Scribner

   The Usual Desire to Kill, by Camilla Barnes

   A good rule of thumb: Any novel that so explicitly references homicide
   in its title is probably a murder mystery, or something to do with
   marriage. In this case, it's the latter, and those violent urges belong
   primarily to the intransigent couple's adult daughter, who has been
   unwillingly conscripted into the role of peacemaker. So don't expect
   premeditated murder, exactly – but there may well be some dialogue
   sharp enough to draw blood in this tragicomic debut novel.
   (BUTTON) Purchase BookThe Usual Desire to Kill by Camilla Barnes
   (BUTTON) close overlay

